# Burn & Build — one repo, separate products

Repo: **`pwa-burn-and-build`** (this workspace)

**Keep top products separate.** Do not merge flows, copy, CTAs, or implementation between them unless the user explicitly asks.

**Product name:** **Menu planner** (folder/URL: `menuplanner/`). Never use “meal planner” in user-facing copy or docs.

---

## Product A — Desktop web app (active build)

**Site:** burnandbuilddiet.com

| Path | Role |
|------|------|
| `landing/` | Marketing → questionnaire |
| `questionnaire/` | Intake → save plan → checkout handoff |
| `createyourfoodplan/` | Plan-ready + Stripe paywall ($149 per program) |
| `program-report/` | Deliverable — projections, plan/servings |
| `menuplanner/` | **Menu planner** shell + Print Assistant |
| `mealplanner/` | Redirect stub only → `/menuplanner/` |
| `server/` | API + SQLite — programs, per-program payment |

**Desktop flow:**
```
Landing → questionnaire → Stripe (per program) → program-report → menuplanner
```

**Return access:** `burnandbuilddiet.com/menuplanner/` + email → unlock planner and paid program(s).

- Each new program = its own Stripe checkout (`programId`).
- **End of desktop product** = menu planner shell.

